        "difficulty": 1,
        "gameFile": null,
        "storyFile": null,
        "storyText": "Reina stepped into the muddy training valley like it was a wrestling mat and studied the first move. A storm timer started, and water rushed downhill, pushed soil loose, and carried tiny rocks into a new channel. Reina called the pattern erosion: land slowly changing when water, wind, and gravity keep working. Her mission was to use strategy, compare faster and slower water, and beat her personal best by explaining why the landform changed. Reina also spotted the review words faster, slowest, add and used them as clue cards for the next challenge. At the finish, Reina won the round by pointing to the evidence: moved soil, shifted sand, and a hill that looked different than before.",
        "storyTitle": "Reina and the Hill That Changed",
